The**Email Unsubscribed**trigger activates a flow whenever a contact opts out or unsubscribes from your email communications. This trigger is useful for automating actions when someone chooses to stop receiving your emails.**Topics Covered:***   [How to Configure Email Unsubscribed Trigger](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780014625689-Email-Unsubscribed#h_01J873E0704AKJYPZCYBW0TMDR)

*   [Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780014625689-Email-Unsubscribed#h_01J873Y9Q1MDQZ7GRMZ2H1MT1G)


### How to Configure Email Unsubscribed Trigger


*   While creating the Trigger Based Flows select**Email Unsubscribed**trigger.

![](./Email Unsubscribed – Salesmate_files/mceclip0.png)


*   Once selected, you would then need to configure the Trigger.

*   As you click on the block, a pop will open to add following details.
    ***Name:**Provide a descriptive name for the trigger.
    ***Description:**Give the brief description of what the trigger does.

![](./Email Unsubscribed – Salesmate_files/mceclip1.png)
